token_lists.title: G̷L̷I̷M̷P̷S̷E̷S̷
token_lists.description: G̷L̷I̷M̷P̷S̷E̷S̷ is my first .gif series and it’s based on the research I have done during 5 months at the Boghossian’s Foundation art residency in Brussels. The first outcome was the exhibition and NFT series “…funny, I don’t remember much about her.”  These works investigate the relation between memory, cultural roots, identity and image.

token_lists.title: Fluid
token_lists.description:
“…humans speculated as to what caused fluid fractal fire lights through the universe unaware they in fact created them through their own minds-eye.”

Our species was not the first to live in a Universe where fractals were a common feature. There is evidence of fractal fire and water lights in ancient cultures of the world- most notably the ancient Greeks and Mayans. It is a curious fact that there are no known remnants of the Mayan fractal lights and there is only one known example of the Greek fractal lights in the form of the famous Greek paintings of Icaros, and the paintings of the ‘star in the cave’ at Lascaux, France.

Relational aesthetic interaction courtesy of Yuichiroh Arai and Google Experiments.
